TY  - JOUR
AU  - Ai, Hengjie
AU  - Croce, Mariano Max
AU  - Diercks, Anthony M
AU  - Li, Kai
T1  - News Shocks and the Production-Based Term Structure of Equity Returns
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhy015
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 31
IS  - 7
SP  - 2423
EP  - 2467
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We propose a production-based general equilibrium model to study the link between timing of cash flows and expected returns, both in the cross-section of stocks and along the aggregate equity term structure. Our model incorporates long-run growth news with time-varying volatility and slow learning about the exposure that firms have with respect to these shocks. Our framework provides a unified explanation of the stylized features of the slope of the term structure of equity returns, its variations over the business cycle, and the negative relationship between cash-flow duration and expected returns in the cross-section of book-to-market-sorted portfolios.Received May 27, 2017; editorial decision October 12, 2017 by Editor Itay Goldstein.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhy015
ER  - 



